packages

library(tidyverse)
library(magrittr)
library(here)
library(ggnewscale)

read data

meta <- read_csv(here("raw_data/tank_metadata.csv"))
counts <- read_csv(here("raw_data/tank_counts.csv"))
ysi <- read_csv(here("raw_data/ysi_data.csv"),locale = locale(encoding = "latin1"))
ysi %<>% rename('temp_f' = 'F-21A104910', "do_per" = "DO %-21A106679", "do_conc" = "DO mg/L-21A106679",
                "ph" = "pH-21B101988", "ph_mv" = "pH mV-21B101988", "chlor_rfu" = "Chlorophyll RFU-21B101736",
                "chlor_conc" = "Chlorophyll ug/L-21B101736")

ysi %<>% mutate(bucket = as.factor(as.numeric(gsub("Tank ", "", Site))))

ysi %<>% mutate(temp_c = (temp_f-32)*(5/9))
meta$bucket <- as.factor(meta$bucket)
counts$bucket <- as.factor(counts$bucket)

Zoop Data

data <- left_join(counts, meta, by = "bucket")
data$community <- as.factor(data$community)
data %<>% mutate(total = rowSums(across(juvenile_daphnia_uninf:cerio_inf)), 
                 daphnia = rowSums(across(juvenile_daphnia_uninf:adult_daphnia_inf)),
                 treatment = paste(community, temp, sep="_"))

Totals

ggplot(data,aes(x=sample_date,y=total, color=bucket))+ geom_point() + geom_line(aes(group = bucket)) + scale_color_discrete() + theme(legend.position = "none") + facet_wrap(vars(community)) 

summary <- data %>% group_by(treatment, sample_date) %>% summarize(mean_juvenile = mean(juvenile_daphnia_uninf),
                                                                mean_adult = mean(adult_daphnia_uninf),
                                                                mean_cerio = mean(cerio_uninf),
                                                                mean_daphnia = mean(daphnia),
                                                                mean_total = mean(total),
                                                                temp = temp,
                                                                community = community)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'treatment', 'sample_date'. You can
## override using the `.groups` argument.
ggplot(summary, aes(x=sample_date,y=mean_total, color = temp)) + geom_point() + geom_line(aes(group=treatment)) + facet_wrap(vars(community))

Juvenile and Adult Ratio

size_ratio <- data %>% mutate(j_a_ratio = juvenile_daphnia_uninf/adult_daphnia_uninf)
ggplot(size_ratio, aes(x=sample_date, y=j_a_ratio, color = community)) + geom_point() + geom_line(aes(group=bucket)) + facet_wrap(vars(temp)) + geom_hline(yintercept=1)

ysi_summ <- ysi %>% group_by(bucket, Date) %>% summarize(temp_f = mean(temp_f),
                                                         temp_c = mean(temp_c),
                                                         do_per = mean(do_per),
                                                         do_conc = mean(do_conc),
                                                         ph = mean(ph),
                                                         ph_mv = mean(ph_mv),
                                                         chlor_rfu = mean(chlor_rfu),
                                                         chlor_conc = mean(chlor_conc))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'bucket'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
ysi_summ %<>% left_join(.,meta, by = "bucket")
ggplot(ysi_summ, aes(x=Date, y=temp_c, color = bucket)) + geom_point() + geom_line(aes(group=bucket)) + scale_color_discrete() + theme(legend.position = "none")
